# OPUS web — database connection template (MacBook Air → Mac Mini PostgreSQL).
# Copy to .env.local for local Next.js; never commit real credentials.
#
# SECURITY_GOVERNANCE.md:
# - Prefer Tailscale hostname/IP for the server; avoid exposing Postgres on the public internet.
# - Production: inject DATABASE_URL via GCP Secret Manager (not committed .env).

# Server-side only (Next.js Route Handlers / Server Actions). Do not prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# Replace placeholders:
#   YOUR_TAILSCALE_OR_LAN_HOST  e.g. mac-mini.tailnet-name.ts.net or 100.x.x.x
#   POSTGRES_USER / POSTGRES_DB / password — must match infrastructure/docker/.env on the server

# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://POSTGRES_USER:POSTGRES_PASSWORD@YOUR_TAILSCALE_OR_LAN_HOST:5432/POSTGRES_DB?sslmode=prefer

# Optional: direct URL for Prisma/Drizzle-style tools (same rules as above)
# DIRECT_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://POSTGRES_USER:POSTGRES_PASSWORD@YOUR_TAILSCALE_OR_LAN_HOST:5432/POSTGRES_DB?sslmode=prefer
